<br>
Whateverthecase, not everyone out there who is not playing a wizard that moment is unappreciative of the wizard class.<br>
<br>
Is my opinion different than the norm because I also play a wizard?  Probably.  Right or wrong, I tend to believe that this is a function of what I know about the wizard class, it's benefits and limitation, rather than a function of some emotional attachment to the wizard class.  <br>
<br>
If I play a warrior now having previously played a wizard and I like having a wizard in my group, and my preference to have a wizard present is based on their contribution (not some funked up emotional attachment to the wizard generated by previous wizard playing experience), then one of two things must be true.  Either a.) Most people running the pickup groups you're looking for are ignorant about you're assets or b.) the groups you're looking for are different than the groups I form in the environments I hunt in (as previously stated, I prefer dungeons).  If we assume that everyone knows what a wizard does best (which isn't true let's just assume for argument), then maybe there's some environments (let's say, sitting in an outdoor zone, not a dungeon, mindlessly doing the pull kill pull kill pull kill routine for hours on end without moving) where a wizard is not preferred.  Okay, if that situation is not one where a wizard is preferred (the static exp grind group where you just sit there in the same spot for six hours straight looking at the same skyline, the same trees, the same everything), we might ask why?  Efficiency?  Adding another melee get's an extra 3 percent experience per group member per hour because of whatever?  Who knows.  More importantly, who cares.  My opinion, I hate those groups anyhow.  I get SO bored of staring at the same things, killing same things, hour after hour.  Is that fun?  If everything you're doing in the game is boring and repetitive, couldn't you just as well be doing a tradeskill?  You're only left with socialization to stimulate you're cerebrial cortex at that point.  Can't you get socialization somewhere else, like a guild?  Or, a dungeon crawl group?  <br>
<br>
When I do play my wizard, I find myself sometimes wanting a group.  Some unusual occasions I've wanted a group... badly, and couldn't find one.  It's times like these that I'll, once in a blue moon, consider a boring, outdoor, exp grind group if one is offered.  But, ya know, I wind up disbanding and either soloing or loggin in my warrior in less than an hour.  Why?  It's SO BORING it borders on being GAY!<br>
<br>
The times I've most enjoyed grouping with my wizard is when I'm either a.) on a big raid or b.) in a dungeon group.  Not only do I find the people who do dungeons (not seb, karnors, or velks mind you, nothing crowded) appreciate my wizard more, but they also tend to be differen types of people, more interesting, and the time I spend in those groups is vastly more enjoyable than an exp grind situation.<br>
<br>
How do I find these groups?  Sometimes, but rarely, guildies.  Mostly I just find a spot I like at first, read up on it, spend some time poking around the dungeon if possible until I bump into a group doing something interesting.  After a while of polite hovering, I usually get invited.  Sometimes I even get invited to full groups as one extra in raid mode ;&gt;)<br>
<br>
Anyways, there's my 2cp.  Hope you get you're spirits up again! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=naenibastra>Naeni Bast Ra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/22/03 8:07:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26204.topic&index=12>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizards just aren't appreciated!</span><hr size=1> Flintnilf has the answer....<br>
