<br>
What are you looking for exactly?  Just to be in a group?  Experience, equipment, friendliness - all of these factor in.  I don't always group where I want to fight because sometimes I go to join friends.  I like to be around people.  Sometimes they come to where I want to fight.<br>
<br>
The first person mentioned not being able to get into a guild.  What kind of guild are you looking for?  I've found that most guilds are political and unless you're well liked you don't get much.  The guild I am in is a family guild.  We don't consider ourself uber.  We don't believe in raiding all the time.  We do believe hunting together.  We believe in giving things to each other and helping others in the world of Norrath as well.  So there is almost always someone I can group with from the guild.<br>
<br>
If there is absolutely no one available or the guild is off fighting (we have a lot of higher levels who can go places I don't go yet) somewhere else I can generally find a group somewhere.  I've gone to the LOY zones and just asked for a camp check and then told to people asking if they'd like to take a level 52 wizzy in and made a few friends that way.  As I've worked on my epic, I've made friends with people needing to slay the same mobs and can check with them if they need help.  I never go LFG.  I just ask people (in tells directly) if they need someone or find a pickup group at zoneline (and then move them to a safer place if that's a rough zoneline with trains).<br>
<br>
I also suggest what someone else suggested.  Put the group together yourself.  I've gone to zones and when I couldn't actually get INTO a group I would ooc group needs such and such classes and then as I got tells I'd have them meet me somewhere and that would work to get a group together.<br>
<br>
Good luck with finding a group.  It's not as hard as you may think. <p>Renia - wizardess of Cazic-Thule<br>
