Make yourself some friends ... oh wait, you missed that part of the game for 61 levels ... well no wonder.  If you pick wizard because of our soloing ability, you get what you deserve.  Now that you are sort of higher level, no one knows who you are and what you can or cannot do, that's why you cannot find group.  Post 60, you get in group by:<br>
- having friends<br>
- having guildmates who are friendly with you<br>
- being high level enough to make you more desirable that other LFGs<br>
- being lucky to be one of the few available when lots of groups are looking for more<br>
<br>
You have no friends, no guild, no tier 2 flag, and too high level that the mid-50s groupies think you'll suck up too much xp in their tier 1 group.  This IS the end game for EQ the single-player game.<br>
<br>
Oh you want positive suggestions?  Forget xp, forget flags, forget grouping.  Go join a mid-50s guild, help out with quest, help out with epic fights, go raid, make some friends.  Welcome to EQ the MMORPG. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=328193"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.geocities.com/hibashirasakai/HibashiraNewHalfSize.txt"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nulland>Nulland</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/22/03 11:50:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26204.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizards</span><hr size=1> I feel your pain.  I'm flagged up to BoT/HoH, but it hasn't done me a bit of good.  I can LFG for hours, while the same three types of classes (melee/healer/slower) get nabbed almost immediately.  So much min/max'ing goes on now, that unless you are well known and have some of the right friends, it just seems near impossible to get *consistent* grouped xp.  After you get passed up so many times for a group, it gets very difficult to not take it personally and develop some angst.<br>
