I literally spent months being helpless, but since last week, I returned to what I knew... soloing.  Part of the reason I abandoned soloing in the first place was all the hype surrounding xp in PoV when grouped (especially since all the solo spots in PoV are so contested).  However, let me assure you, that even though the xp might be better in an IC group in PoV, the xp I get solo is much more consistent, efficient, and dependable.  In less than one week, I have gone from zero xp in 61 to zero xp in 64... in a tier one zone at that.  For me, the only person I can depend on is myself.  It gets boring and lonely, but it is a means to an end... the end being 65, which greatly improves your marketability (or so it seems).<br>
